"Once you go small you'll never go tall!"</i></font><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usnoa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Snoa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/29/01 1:17:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=143.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So away, I solo'd a red Pookha today...</span><hr size=1> I found that the trick to kite a mob is not to take too far of a lead while runnign from it.  Use F11 to to keep an eye on it.  Once it turns around, STOP, TURN AROUND with your /face hotkey, and shoot.  Usually, by the time you land that shot, the mob's hp will be close to dead and it'l be moving like it's snared.  You'll have no problems chasing it down then.<br>
